SIMPLE: unimproved
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unimproved
<hw>Un`im*proved"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
improved; not made better or wiser; not advanced in knowledge, manners,
or excellence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not used; not employed; especially, not used or
employed for a valuable purpose; <as>as, <ex>unimproved</ex>
opportunities; <ex>unimproved</ex> blessings</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not tilled, cultivated, or built upon; yielding no
revenue; <as>as, <ex>unimproved</ex> land or soil</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unimuscular</ent>⟦br⟧
